\pagebreakNum

### Dedicated Weapon
*2nd-level monk feature* <br/>
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

You train yourself to use a variety of weapons as monk weapons, not just simple melee weapons and shortswords. Whenever you finish a short or long rest, you can touch one weapon, focus your chi on it, and then count that weapon as a monk weapon until you use this feature again.

Whenever you finish a short or long rest, you can touch one weapon, or a number of weapons of a single type with the thrown weapon property up to your monk level, and then count that weapon as a monk weapon until you use this feature again. The weapon must be a simple or martial weapon that you are proficient with, and must lack the heavy and special properties. Alternatively, it may be a weapon with both the heavy and reach properties.

### Monastic Style
*3rd-level monk feature* <br/>
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

You commit yourself to a monastic style, a specific method of combat and lifestyle. Three styles, the Way of the Brewmaster, the Way of the Mistweaver, or the Way of the Windwalker are all detailed at the end of the class description. Your style grants you features at 3rd level and again at 6th, 11th, and 17th level.

### Combo Strike
*3rd-level monk feature* <br/>
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

If you spend 1 chi point or more as part of your action on your turn, you can make one attack with an unarmed strike or a monk weapon as a bonus action before the end of the turn.

### Swift Reflexes
*3rd-level monk feature* <br/>
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

In your practice of the martial arts, you have improved your reflexes beyond the norm. You have trained to respond to certain events with startling haste.

You gain two Swift Reflexes of your choice at 3rd level. A list of the available options can be found at the end of this class description. When you gain certain monk levels, you gain additional reflexes of your choice, as shown on the Swift Reflexes column of the Monk table.

Additionally, when you gain a level in this class, you can choose one of the reflexes you know and replace it with another reflex that you could learn at that level.

### Ability Score Improvement
*4th-level monk feature* <br/>
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

When you reach 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase one ability score of your choice by 2, or you can increase two ability scores of your choice by 1. As normal, you can't increase an ability score above 20 using this feature.

