\pagebreakNum

## Changelog V1
A lot of inspiration was taken from kireikasu's work [here](https://www.gmbinder.com/share/-MTlouFHmy1ywgAcT4D3). In general, the monk was redesigned to be less about pandaren zen and monasteries, instead being relatively agnostic in core to allow for more broad multiclass concepts and non-Pandaria based custom subclasses.

### General
- Intimidation and Perception added to the list of skill proficiency options.
- Fixed an odd typo in Martial Arts, listing medium and heavy armor as mail and plate.
- Martial Arts now works with light armor or when using a shield, though the ability to make "no-hand" bonus action unarmed attack does not work while wielding a shield.
- Added the ability to Martial Arts to use Dexterity in place of Strength for grapples and jumps.
- Increased the starting Martial Arts die from d4 to d6, so as not to force players into wielding a weapon for the first couple levels.
- Removed the Chi techniques Effuse, Elusive Dance, and Step of the Wind. The two remaining Chi techniques, Fists of Fury and the new Expel Harm, now also upgrade at 11th level.
- Added Celerity, which is composed of most of the Unarmored Movement feature (now working with light armor and with an upgrade at 15th level) as well as the former Chi technique Step of the Wind (without a chi point cost).
- Removed the 2nd level version of Roll.
- Renamed "Monastic Traditions" to "Monastic Styles," to evoke the concept of things like "Drunken Fist Style" and "Monkey Style."
- Added the Dedicated Weapon ability from Tasha's Cauldron of Everything.
- Removed Serenity from 3rd level.
- Added Swift Reflexes at 3rd level, which is composed of the Deflect Missiles ability from the PHB as well as a melee equivalent of that ability, and some other minor changes.
- Added the Ki-Fueled Attack from Tasha's Cauldron of Everything, renamed as Combo Strike.
- Added Slow Fall back in as Roll, with a second option to reduce damage taken from AoE attacks.
- Added the ability to use Detox on other creatures, at the cost of chi.
- Added Zen Flight at 9th level.
- Removed the old version of Transcendence from 9th level.
- Added Improved Chi Techniques at 11th level.
- Removed Rushing Jade Wind from 13th level.
- Added Spinning Crane Kick at 13th level, which is a slightly modified version of Whirlwind Attack ability from the Ranger: Hunter Conclave in the PHB.
- Added an alternate version of Transcendence at 14th level, using the Spirit Projection ability from the Warlock: Undead patron from Van Richten's Guide to Ravenloft. The only changes were to remove two abilities related to casting spells and a warlock subclass ability.
- Added Touch of Death at 18th level. It is based on Quivering Palm, but being instantaneous, costing more to use, and removing the win-win scenario of either reducing a creature to 0 hit points on a failed save or dealing 10d10 damage on a successful one.
- Changed Perfect Zen to Grand Master, giving a +4 bonus to Wisdom and Dexterity/Strength like the barbarian capstone.

### Subclasses
- Moved the 11th level subclass abilities to 10th level.

## Changelog V1.1
- Added leather armor to their starting equipment
- Added improvised weapons to the list of weapon proficiencies
- Added darts (aka shuriken) to the list of monk weapons, under Martial Arts.
- Moved the ability to use Dexterity for Jump checks to Celerity.
- Re-added unarmored movement's full speed bonus to Celerity. 
- Replaced starting Chi abilities.

